description: The Schaller & Weber Bratwurst follows a recipe brought to the U.S.A. by Ferdinand Schaller. As an apprentice sausage maker in Stuttgart, his charcuterier roots reach back to the 15th-century and the development of this traditional German sausage. The family recipe Ferdinand created, a mixture of pork and veal in a natural casing, gives Schaller & Weber Bratwurst an unmistakeable taste. This perennial best-seller is still one of our favorites. Spiced with nutmeg and marjoram, the sausage has a mild but distinct flavor. They are delicious every time and easy to eat any time. Our cooked brats are great on the grill or year round on the stove. Put them on a bed of sauerkraut with a squirt of Sweet & Spicy Mustard or however you want to serve them.
name: Bratwurst Sausage

description:
Our award winning Arrosticini are a specific type of skewer which are made from Lamb.   A fan favorite for any and every occasion!  Best grilled and simply topped with Mediterranean Sea Salt. The meat is all butchered and skewered by hand into small cubes and placed on a wooden skewer. Between the meat, a small piece of fat is placed to ensure the Lamb stays tender and bursting with flavor. Abruzzo is a rugged, mountainous, and rural region in Italy. Among the many foods of Abruzzo the most well-known is arrosticini, a unique 
skewer of small cubes of lamb, salted and cooked over a furnacell’. D’Abruzzo NYC has become known for its award-winning arrosticini.

Wagyu beef is known for its high level of marbling, which gives it a rich and buttery flavor and makes it incredibly tender and juicy. Allen Brothers Ground Wagyu Beef is a perfect choice for a wide variety of dishes, including burgers, meatballs, and meatloaf. Its rich and beefy flavor is sure to enhance any dish.
name: Ground Wagyu Beef

description: Bone-in Plate Short Rib, a premium quality cut of beef that is perfect for slow-cooking and braising. This exquisite cut is taken from the lower rib section of the cow, and has a rich and beefy flavor that is enhanced by the bone-in cooking process. Bone-in Plate Short Rib has a beautiful marbling of fat and meat that gives it a tender and juicy texture. When cooked low and slow, the meat becomes fall-off-the-bone tender, with a deep and savory flavor that is perfect for a variety of dishes. This cut of beef is versatile and can be used in a variety of ways. It is perfect for stews, pot roasts, and braised dishes, as well as for grilling or smoking. It can also be used in tacos, sandwiches, or other creative dishes.
name: Bone-in Plate Short Rib

description: This signature patty looks, cooks, and tastes like a classic beef burger, but derives its protein content solely from plants. Proudly display this well-known brand on your menu, and vegan and plant-forward patrons will gladly bring their business into your establishment. The foundations of this burger are soy and potato proteins, which provide essential nutrition comparable to animal protein. But the flavor powerhouse that Impossible Foods is known for is heme, a molecule found in both plants and animals that delivers the familiar savory beef flavor that makes this product so closely comparable to traditional burgers. They produce heme by fermenting yeast, creating a rich umami that gives this burger alternative its signature flavor and appearance.
name: 5.33 oz Impossible Burger

description: The Schaller & Weber Bratwurst follows a recipe brought to the U.S.A. by Ferdinand Schaller. As an apprentice sausage maker in Stuttgart, his charcuterier roots reach back to the 15th-century and the development of this traditional German sausage. The family recipe Ferdinand created, a mixture of pork and veal in a natural casing, gives Schaller & Weber Bratwurst an unmistakeable taste. This perennial best-seller is still one of our favorites. Spiced with nutmeg and marjoram, the sausage has a mild but distinct flavor. They are delicious every time and easy to eat any time. Our cooked brats are great on the grill or year round on the stove. Put them on a bed of sauerkraut with a squirt of Sweet & Spicy Mustard or however you want to serve them.
name: Bratwurst Sausage

description: Pork Rack comes from the rib area of the loin, which contains a bit more fat making it super flavorful and tender. An impressive centerpiece roast that is easy to prepare whether roasted in the oven or on the grill. A pork equivalent of a standing beef rib roast or a rack of lamb, this rack of pork comes from Heritage Duroc pork, known for its rich red color and evenly marbled, flavorful meat. Nothing like grocery store pork, Duroc pork has a more delicate meat that will be juicy and tender when cooked to medium rare. Raised in the USA by small family farmers who prioritize animal welfare - hogs are free to roam, fed only a vegetarian diet, and never administered antibiotics or growth promotants. Taste the difference that this superior breed offers.

description: Amazing pork boils down to three factors: Genetics, Lifestyle and diet, which is why Campo Grande lberico comes from heirloom Iberian pings. The incredible marbling and nutty richness make chefs hail lberico as the Wagyu of pork. The natural umami, tenderness, and superior marbling often leaves unsuspecting diners wondering if they were really eating pork, or a fine Wagyu steak. Meaty, savory deliciousness with deep, bold flavors. Incredibly juicy, melt in your mouth tenderness due to its ultra-low melting point leaving you an irresistible aroma which is released when cooking. Spain's best kept culinary secret is Campo Grande pork!

description: BLACK TRUFFLE SALAMI - Truffles, truffles, truffles! Studded with minced black truffles and simply seasoned with black Tellicherry black pepper and truffle-infused salt. Made with heritage Berkshire and Duroc pigs raised on family farms without antibiotics or hormones, and always vegetarian-fed. Our family is from Southern Italy, but we have friends from many regions. Tuscany is known for producing both black and white truffles and we are happy to partner with our friends at Savini Tartufi in Tuscany to feature their black truffles and truffle salt in our Tartufo salame. We aren’t fans of many truffle products because the strong essence of artificial truffle-like oils overpowers quality products. We believe using natural products best enhances the excellent quality of our pork, so we keep it simple, and delicious!
name: Tartufo Salami

description: Chicken Feet, a high-quality ingredient that is perfect for adding a unique and savory flavor to your dishes. Chicken feet are a popular ingredient in many cuisines around the world, and are often used for making rich and flavorful stocks, broths, and soups. Chicken Feet have a distinctive texture and flavor that is rich and savory. They are high in collagen, which gives them a gelatinous texture when cooked, making them perfect for adding body and depth to your dishes. Chicken feet are versatile and can be used in a variety of ways. They are perfect for making chicken stock or broth, as well as for adding flavor to stews, soups, and curries. They can also be used in creative dishes like chicken feet dim sum or fried chicken feet.

description: Semi-boneless butterflied quail is a premium quality culinary product that is perfect for a wide range of dishes. These quail birds are expertly prepared by removing the backbone and breastbone while leaving the wings and legs attached, resulting in a flattened bird that cooks quickly and evenly. Semi-boneless butterflied quail has a rich and flavorful taste, with tender and juicy meat that is perfect for grilling, roasting, or pan-searing. It has a mild gamey flavor with hints of sweetness and is often described as a cross between chicken and duck meat.

description: For more than 30 years Fabrique Delices has been preparing time-honored classics alongside innovative new products. Made in small batches the Artisanal and Traditional way, according to Authentic French recipes. We take pride in sourcing the finest ducks, known for their tender and flavorful meat. Our commitment to quality ensures every bite is a symphony of rich, authentic flavors. Rooted in centuries-old French tradition, our Duck Rillettes is a testament to the art of preservation. Succulent duck meat is slowly simmered, gently rendered, and expertly seasoned to create a luxurious and velvety texture. From being a star on charcuterie boards to enhancing gourmet sandwiches, pastries, or as a standalone delicacy, our Duck Rillettes is a versatile ingredient that inspires culinary innovation.

description: Fra' Mani Handcrafted Salumi's Classic Mortadella is made with prime cuts from the leg, shoulder, and belly, carefully trimmed by hand. Minutely fine-ground, with no artificial additives. Speckled with small cubes of pork jowl, the firmest and most flavorful fat on the hog. Slow-roasted for 10 hours with dry heat and finished with a breath of natural fruitwood smoke. Like the classic version of Mortadella di Bologna, Fra' Mani Classic Mortadella contains no pistachio nuts. Each piece is about 6 pounds.
name: Mortadella

description: The double smoked, applewood smoked Boneless Ham is an American Classic. Exceptionally lean pork is selected and brined in a secret blend of spices and maple syrup for days. Once the curing process is completed the Hams are placed in our German smokehouses for hours to in order to deliver a rich smokiness that chefs search the world over for. The density of the smoke complements the sweetness of the ham to create a truly spectacular ham.

description: For over 100 years, Leoncini has been the epitome of Italian artistry, renowned for their exquisite Mortadella. Crafted from pigs born, bred, and processed in Italy, this Optima Mortadella represents the pinnacle of their dedication. Butchers meticulously inspect and prepare the pork, achieving the ideal blend of leg, shoulder, and belly. Slow-cooked in traditional masonry ovens, it boasts a lusciously creamy texture and an impeccably clean pork flavor.

description: Leoncini Prosciutto Cotto, a premium quality deli meat that is perfect for adding a savory and smoky flavor to your dishes. This exquisite ham is made from high-quality pork that is cooked slowly with aromatic herbs and spices, creating a delicious and satisfying taste. Leoncini Prosciutto Cotto has a beautiful pinkish color and a rich aroma of smokiness and spices. It has a tender and juicy texture that melts in your mouth, making it perfect for sandwiches, salads, or any dish that requires a rich and flavorful ham. This prosciutto cotto is versatile and can be used in a variety of ways. It is perfect for making classic ham sandwiches, or for using in creative dishes like ham and cheese croissants, ham and potato soup, or ham and mushroom quiche.
name: Prosciutto Cotto

description: Schaller & Weber New York Style Pastrami is a harmonious blend of top-quality beef, a proprietary spice rub, and a smoking process that imparts a bold, smoky flavor. Each tender, thinly sliced bite is a celebration of savory richness that embodies the essence of New York's deli heritage. We believe in preserving the art of traditional pastrami-making, and our New York Style Pastrami is a testament to that commitment. Each cut is meticulously trimmed, expertly seasoned, and smoked to perfection, embodying the expertise, precision, and authenticity that define Schaller & Weber.  Create classic pastrami sandwiches with all the fixings, add it to gourmet salads, or craft unique appetizers that showcase its bold, smoky flavor.
name: New York City Pastrami

description: Schaller & Weber French Bistro Ham is a harmonious blend of premium pork, expertly cured and seasoned with a traditional French touch. Each slice is a celebration of rich, savory flavors that transport your taste buds to the cozy bistros of France. We believe in preserving the art of traditional ham-making, and our French Bistro Ham is a testament to that commitment. Meticulously cured and carefully seasoned, it embodies the expertise, precision, and authenticity that define Schaller & Weber. Create classic Croque Monsieur sandwiches, add it to quiches and omelets, or use it as a flavorful ingredient in salads and appetizers.
name: French Bistro Ham
